Preheat your #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Halve the @potatoes{450%grams} lengthways and pop them onto a #baking tray{}. Drizzle
with @oil{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Rub the oil over the potatoes,
then lay them cut-side down.

Bake on the top shelf of your oven until tender and a knife slips in easily,
~{30-40%minutes}.

Meanwhile, drain and rinse the @mixed beans{1%carton} in a #sieve{}.

Put a large #saucepan{} on medium heat with a drizzle of @oil{}. Add the
@diced chorizo{90%grams} and fry until starting to brown, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add the @tomato passata{1%carton}, @chipotle paste{20%grams} (add less if you'd
prefer things milder), @vegetable stock paste{10%grams}, mixed beans,
@sugar{1/2%tsp} and @water{50%milliliters} for the sauce. Stir to combine.

Bring the chorizo chilli to the boil, then lower the heat. Pop a lid on the pan
(or cover with #foil{}) and simmer until thickened, ~{7-9%minutes}.

While the chilli cooks, in a #medium bowl{}, combine the @coleslaw mix{120%grams}
and @burger sauce{30%grams}. Season with salt and pepper and set aside.

Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60%grams}.

Once the chilli has thickened, remove from the heat and stir through the
@red pepper chilli jelly{25%grams}. Season with salt and pepper, then set aside
with the lid on to keep warm.

Reheat the chilli a few mins before the jacky-Ps are ready (if needed).

Once the jacky-Ps are ready, remove from the oven and spread the
@butter{10%grams} over the cut side of the potatoes. Roughly mash it into each
potato with a #fork{}.

Share the jacky-Ps out between your plates. Spoon the beans over the potatoes.

Top with a dollop of @soured cream{75%grams} and the grated cheese.

Serve the slaw alongside. Enjoy!